Installing Syslack Linux Is Extremely Hard TO Install Unless if You use Ubuntu Server install

1 Download Ubuntu Server Iso From https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Flash Iso Using BalenaEtcher Rufus dd mode Or Ventoy
3 Boot from an Ubuntu Server ISO or a debootstrap‑based live environment.
  Switch to tty2 (Ctrl+Alt+F2) Then run sudo passwd root then set your root password
4 Run Root using su -
4 Locales and Mirrors
  Generate locales manually:
  dpkg-reconfigure locales
5 Edit /etc/apt/sources.list using sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list to point to Ubuntu mirrors Then
  deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble main universe multiverse restricted
  deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble-updates main universe multiverse restricted
  deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble-security main universe multiverse restricted
6 Disk Configuration (fdisk + ext4 + swap)
  fdisk -l
  Partition manually:

  /dev/sda1 → EFI (if UEFI, 512MB, type EF00)

  /dev/sda2 → root (ext4, rest of disk)

  /dev/sda3 → swap (2–4GB depending on RAM)
7 Format:
  mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
  mkdir /mnt/boot
  mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/boot   # only if UEFI
8 Base System Install
  Bootstrap Ubuntu into /mnt:
  debootstrap --arch=amd64 noble /mnt http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
  Mount pseudo‑filesystems:
  
  mount -t proc /proc /mnt/proc
  mount -t sysfs /sys /mnt/sys
  mount --bind /dev /mnt/dev

  Enter chroot:
  chroot /mnt /bin/bash
9 Installing Bootloader
  For Legacy BIOS (Syslinux)
  apt install syslinux
  syslinux --install /dev/sda
  UEFI (GRUB):
  apt install grub-efi-amd64
  grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot --bootloader-id=Syslack
  update-grub
10 Unified Kernel Images
   apt install linux-image-generic-lts
   Enable unified kernel images (UKI) if desired
   Configure systemd-boot or GRUB with UKI entries in /boot/efi/EFI/Syslack/
11 Identity Rituals
   Set hostname
   echo "yourname" > /etc/hostname

   Create user account:
   adduser yourname
   usermod -aG sudo yourname

   Configure timezone
   dpkg-reconfigure tzdata

   Configure network manually
   Edit /etc/netplan/config.yaml
   netplan apply
12 Finalization
   Update package lists
   apt update && apt upgrade

  Exit chroot and unmount
  exit
  umount -R /mnt
13 Reboot into Syslack Linux.
14 This Is Unfinished
